<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:58:49 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>关于联邦大陪审团需要了解什么</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/27/what-to-know-about-federal-grand-juries/</link><description>在美国，联邦大陪审团每年起诉数万人。</description><pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:58:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/27/what-to-know-about-federal-grand-juries/</guid></item><item><title>大多数住在家里的老年人都希望在原地安享晚年，但他们并不完全有信心自己能做到这一点</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/26/most-older-adults-who-live-at-home-want-to-age-in-place-but-they-arent-entirely-confident-theyll-get-to/</link><description>高收入老年人最有可能表示他们更愿意转向辅助生活。</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 09:45:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/26/most-older-adults-who-live-at-home-want-to-age-in-place-but-they-arent-entirely-confident-theyll-get-to/</guid></item><item><title>老龄化美国的家庭护理</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/02/26/family-caregiving-in-an-aging-america/</link><description>随着美国人口老龄化，家庭成员越来越多地照顾年迈的父母或配偶。护理人员的经历因性别而异。</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 09:30:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2026/02/26/family-caregiving-in-an-aging-america/</guid></item><item><title>对于许多美国黑人来说，家庭超越了出生和法律关系</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/race-and-ethnicity/2026/02/25/for-many-black-americans-family-extends-beyond-birth-and-legal-ties/</link><description>美国黑人与他们视为家人的亲戚和非亲戚分享情感和经济支持。</description><pubDate>Thu, 26 Feb 2026 12:34:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/race-and-ethnicity/2026/02/25/for-many-black-americans-family-extends-beyond-birth-and-legal-ties/</guid></item><item><title>谁认为自己的一方在政治上获胜或失败，党派分歧严重</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/24/stark-partisan-divide-in-who-thinks-their-side-is-winning-and-losing-in-politics/</link><description>在我们提出这个问题的十年里，美国人总体上更有可能说他们的球队正在输，而不是说他们赢了。</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:33:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/24/stark-partisan-divide-in-who-thinks-their-side-is-winning-and-losing-in-politics/</guid></item><item><title>青少年如何使用和看待人工智能</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/02/24/how-teens-use-and-view-ai/</link><description>超过一半的美国青少年表示他们曾使用聊天机器人来帮助完成学业，12% 的青少年表示他们从这些工具中获得了情感支持。青少年倾向于更积极地看待人工智能未来对他们生活的影响，而不是消极地看待。</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2026 12:18:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/internet/2026/02/24/how-teens-use-and-view-ai/</guid></item><item><title>2026 年国情咨文：美国人在国家面临的关键问题上的立场</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/23/state-of-the-union-2026-where-americans-stand-on-key-issues-facing-the-nation/</link><description>在国情咨文发布之前，以下是根据皮尤研究中心最近的调查得出的美国公众对关键政策问题的看法。</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Feb 2026 12:34:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/23/state-of-the-union-2026-where-americans-stand-on-key-issues-facing-the-nation/</guid></item><item><title>电子邮件通讯作为新闻来源</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/2026/02/19/email-newsletters-as-a-source-of-news/</link><description>十分之三的美国成年人表示，他们至少有时会从时事通讯中获取新闻，但许多人并没有阅读他们收到的大部分时事通讯。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 12:28:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/journalism/2026/02/19/email-newsletters-as-a-source-of-news/</guid></item><item><title>美国哪些宗教团体受教育程度最高？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/19/which-us-religious-groups-are-most-highly-educated/</link><description>印度教徒和犹太人比其他宗教团体的美国人更有可能获得四年制大学学位。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 12:13:45 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/02/19/which-us-religious-groups-are-most-highly-educated/</guid></item><item><title>是什么让人们为自己的国家感到自豪？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/02/17/what-makes-people-proud-of-their-country/</link><description>从印度尼西亚的多样性到法国的美食，25 个国家的人们用自己的语言分享了令他们感到自豪的事情。</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Feb 2026 12:36:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2026/02/17/what-makes-people-proud-of-their-country/</guid></item></channel></rss>